                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I actually play a Conjurer in EQ2 - not a chanter.  The Conjurer boards have mixed feelings about the changes, but mostly there isn't a "The Sky is Falling" mentality.  Conjurer's have alot of broken spells including fire and water pets that completely broken, and they expecting future tweaks in those pets.  What's my point?  SOE isn't done and I suspect/expect enchanters and summoners to be tweaked up in many aspects once the wizards are re-tweaked.
<br />

<br />
ALSO:
<br />
YAY for the removal of interdependency!
<br />
I'd feel bad for the alchemists execpt now they are in the same boat my poor level 20 Sage has been in since the beginning, so excuse me if my sympathy doesn't abound.
<br />

<br />
One chemist was complaining he'd have to give up his 3 floor 6 plat a week house now that his WORT business is gone - WAH!  Cry me a river.  The fact that anyone could have a 6 plat a week house and be able to maintain it 3 months after the game opened shows how broken the current system was.
<br />

<br />
