                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The tradeskill fuel cost changes are a downright abominable idea.  It was bad enough getting price-gouged by greedy alchemists, but is it any better to pay even more to society venders for fuel?  The interdependency fix is crippled by the fact that you will be required to use more fuel in these new recipes, all of which will cost more, thanks to the fuel cost changes.
<br />

<br />
Tanks won't be tanking better with the mitigation boosts they talked about in the patch message, because their avoidance got trashed in the changes not mentioned in the patch message.
<br />

<br />
Avoidance is way out of whack anyway; my Light Armor-wearing Fury can pull two or three Green ^ and ^^ group encounters and kill them all fairly easily.  It's all about level and has nothing to do with gear or ability.  I simply chose an overpowered racial tradition that boosted my Defense by 5, enabling me to tank the lowest level Green group cons (^, ^^, it doesn't really matter) as if they were Grey cons.  That particular tradition was somewhat balanced when it was a triggered ability that only lasted a minute and had a 30 minute reuse but is broken now that it is a passive boost that is always active.
<br />

<br />
Amen on soloing high orange and low red Solo encounters.  All it takes is cycling HOs over and over and staying alive.  Red Solo encounters hit for less than Green Group encounters so staying alive is not an issue, especially if you can heal yourself (eg: Priest, Crusader).</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
